# ─── Supabase (optional — enables Google OAuth sign-in) ──────────────────────
# Create a project at https://supabase.com, enable Google OAuth provider,
# then copy these values from Settings > API.
#
# Development: set these as env vars before running `cargo tauri dev`.
# Production:  set these at compile time — they are baked into the binary
#              via option_env!() during `cargo tauri build`.
#
# The anon key is a PUBLIC client key by Supabase design.
# Security is enforced by Row Level Security (RLS) and OAuth tokens.
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...

# ─── Google OAuth (credential design flows) ──────────────────────────────────
# Create a "Desktop" OAuth 2.0 Client in GCP Console.
# Client secrets for desktop apps are NOT confidential (per Google's OAuth docs).
#
# Development: place in .env at project root, or set as env vars.
# Production:  baked into binary at compile time via option_env!().
GCP_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GCP_CLIENT_SECRET=GOCSPX-...

# ─── Sentry (production only — do NOT set locally) ───────────────────────────
# Error reporting is designed to track installer/release builds only. Do NOT
# set SENTRY_DSN or VITE_SENTRY_DSN in local .env — code guards in main.rs and
# src/lib/sentry.ts force a no-op in debug/dev builds anyway, but keeping the
# values out of .env avoids baking the DSN into locally-built binaries.
#
# Production: set as GitHub Secrets (SENTRY_DSN, SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN,
#             SENTRY_ORG, SENTRY_PROJECT). Injected by release.yml at build
#             time. Source maps are uploaded in CI.
# See docs/devops/guide-error-reporting.md.

# ─── Tauri Updater Signing (CI-only — not needed for local dev) ───────────────
# Ed25519 keypair for signing update bundles. Generate with:
#   npx @tauri-apps/cli signer generate -w ~/.tauri/personas.key
# Set as GitHub Secrets: TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY, TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD
# The public key lives in src-tauri/tauri.conf.json under plugins.updater.pubkey.

# ─── Frontend build configuration (optional) ─────────────────────────────────
# Feature tier — compiled into the build when set. When unset, the bundle
# includes all tiers and users can switch at runtime via Settings > Account.
#   starter  — end-user view only (agents, credentials, messages, templates)
#   team     — adds events, pipelines, deployment, analytics
#   builder  — adds dev tools, lab, design system (default superset)
# VITE_APP_TIER=builder

# Inbound webhook trigger server base URL. The Rust backend binds the webhook
# listener to this host:port. Change only if port 9420 is occupied.
# VITE_WEBHOOK_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9420

# Mobile platform override — only set for Android / iOS builds. Omit for desktop.
# VITE_PLATFORM=

# Bundle analyzer — when set, `npm run build` emits dist/bundle-report.html.
# ANALYZE=true
